definitions.definition: To provide an impetus for motion or physical action; to cause to move in a certain direction; to drive or push forward.
To provide an impetus for nonphysical change; to cause to arrive to a certain situation or result.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To provide an impetus for motion or physical action; to cause to move in a certain direction; to drive or push forward.
secondary_definitions: ( transitive , figurative ) To provide an impetus for nonphysical change; to cause to arrive to a certain situation or result.
